        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         While it's true that we turn HPs into mana, it doesn't mean that the more HPs we have means we have more mana.</P><P>Having a large number of HPs just allows us to lich for longer before we have to tap back life.  We still regen mana at the same rate no matter how many HPs we have so our mana pool doesn't actually increase just because we have uber HPs.</P><P>Know what I mean?  It is important to have a nice pool of HPs but regen os the real key here.</P><P>As for your question, I can see arguments to go with either ring.  If you find yourself runing low on mana alot, then go with the extra mana.  If not, then go with the extra HPs so you can lich longer.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97736" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.facepics.com/profiles/images/alaughery/alaughery_image3.jpg" border=0></a><br>47 Gnecromancer</P><P>Edited by - Corto on 08/16/2002  12:13:24<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
