        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         You are absolutely correct, in that sense having more HPs does help.</P><P>But I think of it this way...</P><P>Necro 1 = 3000 HPs<BR>Necro 2 = 2000 HPs<BR>Both have the same amount of mana.</P><P>Necro 1 and 2 can both cast the same amount of spells before going OOM.  Then while they med they both lose HPs at the same pace (lets assume same level and equipment).  So now bith necros medded to full and Necro 1 still has 1000HPs while necro 2 is out of HPs.  They are still both short 2000HPs from full.  They both still at some point have to tap back 2000HPs.  Sure Necro 1 can wait a little longer to start tapping, but then he'll need to tap back just that many more HPs.</P><P>Anyways, that's the way I look at it.  Wether I have 1000HPs or 3000HPs I still lose them at the same rate when medding, and still have to tap them back.  The difference is that I'm either tapping back 1000HPs or I'm tapping back 3000HPs.</P><P>I like having a lot of HPs so don't get me wrong.  But for me it's more so I can take a couple more blows to the head from uber_mob_01, and also so I don't kill myself as fast going afk while liching.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97736" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.facepics.com/profiles/images/alaughery/alaughery_image3.jpg" border=0></a><br>47 Gnecromancer<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
