         BoD fills a little over 2 bubs of health when liching. over 2.5 when not. I have no problem letting my health drop to 2 bubs (or near it) before casting BoD when solo or with a group of long time friends, but try explaining that to a pick up group or any cleric for that matter. Not advisable on summoning mobs either or areas where wandering adds can get in a smack before crowd control can take care of it (and if you're the crowd control then you really want to avoid chances of getting low health agro)</P><P>HP>Mana for one simple reason imo---I dont have to get so low in health before I can get full effect from that BoD. Therefore my survivability chances have just greatly increased.</P><P>just my 2cp</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_blank">Charbonez Soulmark</a><BR>Duzzil Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
