		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=6142"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=6142')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=59959&amp;TOPIC_ID=7254&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=HP+vs+Mana&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         HPs > All -- hands down, by far, end of discussion.</P><P>The way HPs increases a necromancers power is a bit subtle and has been touched on some but I will explain it from the way I see it.  First off, hps have nothing to do with how fast you regenerate mana, neither does mana for that matter. It isnt really relative.  Mana effeciency and regain has to do with focus effects and FT items.</P><P>Most liches strive for effeciency.  And one way to do that is to only use vex/bod or taps when u are low enough on life so you dont cause your heals/taps to go to waste.  You want ALL of that tap to heal so you can once again convert it to mana. So what this means is the lich with 2000hps would have to wait till he was at 900hps 45%health before he could cast vex and use it effeciently. While the necromancer with 3000hps would still have 1900hps 63%health when he cast the vex.  It is basically a cushion for how we throw our life around....either converting it to mana, tapping it back, or transfering it to someone else via pacts.  We all have a point on our health bar we feel uncomfortable with.  With more hps it takes alot longer to reach that point.  End result being, you die less, and you click off lich alot less because you have dipped below the safety zone. </P><P>Bottom line is that you die less, have alot more flexibility with how you toss your life around and suck it back, and if you ever do have to actually stop and med up some period of time you have alot more mana stored within your precious HP pool which allows u to utilize liching longer...mana comes from HP pool ALOT faster than from straight medding.  Adding HPs is adding to that HP pool...Furthermore...mana doesnt do much for us...we regain it very fast....and because we utilize alot of effecient and slow methods of killing coupled with insane mana regen....running out of mana shouldnt be much of an issue if you have a reasonable amount.</P><P>When considering straight stats (no effects) I rank them like this:<BR>1. HPs<BR>2. STA<BR>2. MR<BR>4. FR/CR<BR>5. PR/DR<BR>6. MANA<BR>7. INT<BR>8. AC<BR>9. AGI</P><P>Others dont mean shit </P><P><img src="http://ourworld.cs.com/bgrmail/zorlak.jpg" border=0></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

